  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Acompanamiento Emocional Humanitario a comunidades embera desplazadas a catru y zonas aledanas por la violencia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will be adapted from ACOPLE, an existing program developed for Afro-Colombian IDPs that HAI is implementing in Quibd&#xF3;, and that uses evidence-based interventions for depression and Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD). 

In response to identified humanitarian needs on the mental health and psychosocoial front, our team of psychologists will provide individual psychological accompaniment to the community using therapy most appropriate to each project beneficiary. Additionally, HAI will build the capacity within the community to give peer emotional accompaniment by training four Embera psychosocial workers to provide individual and group psychosocial services, and to reduce the risk and prevalence of gender-based violence and suicide.</narrative>
  </description>
